Title : Nick Cordero
Text : {{short description|Canadian actor and singer}}
'''Nick Cordero''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] actor. He appeared on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] in 2014 in the musical ''[[Bullets Over Broadway (musical)|Bullets Over Broadway]]'' in the role of Cheech,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/186325-Woody-Allen-Musical-Bullets-Over-Broadway-With-Zach-Braff-and-Marin-Mazzie-Begins-March-11?tsrc=hph | title=Woody Allen Musical Bullets Over Broadway, With Zach Braff and Marin Mazzie, Begins March 11 | publisher=[[Playbill]] | work=playbill.com | date=11 March 2014 | accessdate=30 April 2014 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502004336/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/186325-Woody-Allen-Musical-Bullets-Over-Broadway-With-Zach-Braff-and-Marin-Mazzie-Begins-March-11?tsrc=hph | archivedate=2 May 2014 | df= }}</ref> for which he was nominated for the [[Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Musical]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/culture/la-et-cm-tony-awards-bullets-over-broadway-20140429,0,7978720.story | title=Tony Awards 2014: 'Bullets over Broadway' has lackluster showing | publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]] | work=latimes.com | date=29 April 2014 | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> and the [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Featured Actor in a Musical]].<ref>Gans, Andrew. [http://www./news/article/190419-2014-Annual-Drama-Desk-Awards-Nominations-Announced-Gentlemans-Guide-Earns-12-Nominations "2014 Annual Drama Desk Awards Nominations Announced; 'Gentleman's Guide' Earns 12 Nominations"], playbill.com, April 25, 2014</ref> He won the Outer Critics Circle Award for Outstanding Featured Actor in a Musical and a Theater World Award for the role.  He originated the title role in the [[Off-Broadway]] production of ''[[The Toxic Avenger (musical)|The Toxic Avenger]]''. He also played the role of Dennis in ''[[Rock of Ages (musical)|Rock of Ages]]'' on Broadway in 2012 and on tour.<ref>[http://www.broadwayworld.com/people/Nick-Cordero/#.U2U-tPldUgR] broadwayworld.com</ref> In March 2016, he joined the Broadway production of ''[[Waitress (musical)|Waitress]]'', playing the role of Earl.<ref name="earl">{{cite web | url=http://www.playbill.com/article/bullets-over-broadway-star-nick-cordero-joins-broadway-bound-waitress-musical | title=Bullets Over Broadway Star Nick Cordero Joins Broadway-Bound Waitress Musical | publisher=[[Playbill]] | work=playbill.com | date=12 January 2016 | accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> He left ''Waitress'' to join the Broadway premiere of the musical ''[[A Bronx Tale (play)|A Bronx Tale]]'', as "Sonny"  at the [[Longacre Theatre]] starting on November 3, 2016.<ref>[http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Nick-Cordero-Richard-H-Blake-Bobby-Conte-Thornton-Ariana-DeBose-and-More-to-Lead-A-BRONX-TALE-on-Broadway-20160831 "Nick Cordero, Richard H. Blake, Bobby Conte Thornton, Ariana DeBose and More to Lead 'A Bronx Tale' on Broadway"] broadwayworld.com, August 31, 2016</ref> In 2017 he portrayed the role of Victor Lugo in [[Blue Bloods (season 8)#ep165|"Heavy is the Head"]] the 10th episode of the 8th season of the [[CBS]] police procedural drama ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]'' and reprised the role in 2018 in [[Blue Bloods (season 8)#ep175|"Your Six"]] the 20th episode of the 8th season of the show.

==Personal life==
Cordero grew up in [[Hamilton, Ontario]]. He attended [[Ryerson University]] for two years and left to perform in the band Lovemethod.<ref>Champion, Lindsay.[http://www.broadway.com/buzz/175841/tony-nominated-bullets-star-nick-cordero-on-quitting-school-getting-in-trouble-woody-allens-comedy-tips/ Tony-Nominated Bullets Star Nick Cordero on Quitting School, Getting in Trouble & Woody Allen's Comedy Tips"] broadway.com, May 8, 2014</ref>

